        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 11 at 4:33PM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 432 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 6 miles northeast of Minden to 12 miles
southwest of Jonesboro. Movement was east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Ruston, Grambling, Jonesboro, Homer, Arcadia, Gibsland, Simsboro,
Chatham, Hodge, North Hodge, Vienna, Evergreen, East Hodge, Lucky,
Athens, Bienville, Lisbon, Quitman, Bryceland, and Mount Lebanon.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

These storms may intensify, so be certain to monitor local radio
stations and available television stations for additional information
and possible warnings from the National Weather Service.</instruction>
